Preheat your oven to 200°C. Chop the @potatoes{450%g} into 2cm wide wedges (no need to peel) and pop on a #baking tray{}. Drizzle with oil, season with @salt{} and @pepper{} and toss to coat. Spread out and roast on the top shelf of your oven until golden, ~{25-30%minutes}, turning halfway.

Meanwhile, pop the @British beef mince{240%g} in a #bowl{} along with half the @Sriracha sauce{1/2%tsp} and 0.5 tbsp per person of pineapple juice. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then use your hands to combine well. Shape into 1 burger per person (make them about the same width as the buns) then set aside on a #plate{}.

> IMPORTANT: Remember to wash your hands after handling raw meat!

Set aside 1 slice of @pineapple rings{2} per person, then drain and roughly chop the rest. Cut 1 slice of @tomato{1%medium}(sliced) per person and set aside, then chop the rest into 2cm chunks. Trim the root from the @baby gem lettuce{1}, remove and reserve one leaf per person, then halve the lettuce lengthways and thinly slice widthways.

== Coleslaw ==

In a large bowl, combine the @red wine vinegar{12%ml}, @sesame oil{12%ml} and a pinch of @salt{} and @pepper{}. Add the chopped pineapple, chopped tomatoes, chopped lettuce and @coleslaw mix{120%g}. Toss to coat then set aside.

== Burger Components ==

Grate the @mature cheddar cheese{60%g}(grated) and split open the @burger buns{2}. In a small bowl, combine the @mayonnaise{1} with the remaining @Sriracha sauce{1/2%tsp}.

Heat a splash of oil in a #frying pan{} on medium-high heat. When hot, add the pineapple rings and @British streaky bacon{4%slices} to the pan. Cook until the pineapple is golden and the bacon is cooked through, ~{2-3%minutes} each side. Transfer to a plate and wrap with #foil{}. Keep the heat high and lay in the burgers. Fry until browned on the outside, ~{2%minutes} each side. Lower the heat to medium and cook for a further ~{3-4%minutes} each side.

> IMPORTANT: The burgers are cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

When the burgers are cooked, remove the pan from the heat. Divide the cheese between each burger. Cover the pan with foil - this will allow the cheese to melt. Meanwhile, warm the buns in your oven for ~{1-2%minutes}.

Divide the wedges and salad between your plates. Spread a little sriracha mayo in each bun then fill with lettuce, tomato, bacon, the burger and pineapple slice. Serve the remaining sriracha mayo alongside. Enjoy!